<P>To &s;hew that the &s;en&s;e of relation&s;hip was not, in tho&s;e days, &s;oon worn out, Mr. <HI>Done,</HI> of <HI>Utkinton,</HI> &s;ent a veni&s;on, for which the &s;heriff gave as a fee 6 <HI>s.</HI> 8 <HI>d.</HI> to the keeper. This &s;heriff was in re&s;pect to the donor fifth in de&s;cent from the marriage of <HI>David Pennant ap Tudor,</HI> with <HI>Anne,</HI> daughter of <HI>John Done,</HI> of <HI>Utkinton,</HI> as near as I can gue&s;s about the year 1440.</P>
