<DIV3 N="4" TYPE="section">
<HEAD>IV.</HEAD>
<P><HI>ETHELYSTAN GLODRYDD,</HI> (the fourth Royal Tribe) Prince of the <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">The country between the&s;e two rivers was anciently called <HI>Ferlys;</HI> and it had its own princes, independent of the princes of <HI>South Wales.</HI></NOTE> country between <HI>Wye</HI> and <HI>Severn.</HI> He was the &s;on of <HI>Cyhelyn ap Ifor,</HI> by <HI>Rhiengar,</HI> the daughter and heir of <HI>Gronw ap Tudor Trevor,</HI> from whom he had derived to him the title of the earldom of <HI>Hereford. Athel&s;tan,</HI> King of <HI>England,</HI> was his god-father.&mdash;<HI>Ethely&s;tan,</HI> (or, as he is &s;ometimes called,
<PB N="287" REF="305">
<HI>Ely&s;tan) b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e two coats quartered, azure, three <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> heads caboched &s;able, langued gules, tu&s;ked or.</HI> His mother's <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">, <HI>parted per bend &s;ini&s;ter ermine and ermines; over all a lion rampant or.</HI></P>
