<ITEM><LABEL>POWELL <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">Of this family was <HI>Richard Powell</HI> of <HI>Ednop,</HI> (or, as it is &s;ometimes written, <HI>Edenhope</HI>) the poet, author of the <HI>Pentarchia,</HI> a &s;hort hi&s;tory, in coar&s;e Latin ver&s;e, of the royal tribes of <HI>Cambria,</HI> and their de&s;cendants. The above-mentioned poem was compo&s;ed about the year 1623. Prefixed to it is a dedi|cation to the then Prince of <HI>Wales,</HI> afterwards <HI>Charles</HI> the Fir&s;t.</NOTE>,</LABEL> of <HI>W<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">yn</HI> and <HI>Ednop, Shrop&s;hire.</HI></ITEM>
