<DIV3 N="13" TYPE="section">
<HEAD>XIII.</HEAD>
<P><HI>EDNOWAIN BENDEW</HI> was Lord of <HI>Tegaingle</HI> in the year of our Lord 1079, (as the book of <HI>Ednop</HI> &s;aith.) He is &s;aid by <HI>Peter Ellis,</HI> the coun&s;ellor, to be the chief of the fifteen tribes. Of him are de&s;cended <HI>Ithel ap Rotpert,</HI> Archdeacon of <HI>Tegaingle,</HI>
<PB N="309" REF="328">
the <HI>Bithels,</HI> and a great many worthy families be&s;ides.&mdash;<HI>He bear|the argent, between three boars heads, a cheveron &s;able.</HI></P>
<P>THE re&s;idence of <HI>Ednowain</HI> is &s;uppo&s;ed by &s;ome to have been at <HI>Ty-maen,</HI> in the pari&s;h of <HI>Whiteford,</HI> (&s;ee p. 119.)</P>
